---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Work with me | Igor Tarasenko"
  description="Short engagements for AI features stuck between a demo and production. Hourly help via Codementor, or a direct call."
>
  <Header />
  <div class="grid">
    <main id="main-content" class="content prose">
      <h1 class="page-h1">Work with me</h1>

      <p class="page-lede">
        Short engagements for AI features stuck between a demo and production.
      </p>

      <h2>The two things people pay for</h2>

      <p>
        <strong>An hour or two.</strong> You bring a repo, a failing agent
        loop, a vague Upwork scope, or a decision you&rsquo;re circling. I look
        at the real failure mode instead of the symptom. You leave with code,
        notes, or a clear next move.
        <br />
        <a href="https://www.codementor.io/@saik0s">Book on Codementor &rarr;</a>
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>A two-to-six week engagement.</strong> Same starting point,
        but I stay in the repo: ship the PRs, wire the evals, set up the
        guardrails, write the runbook your team can own once I leave.
        Engagements are fixed-fee, scope-locked. No retainer creep.
        <br />
        <a href="mailto:igor@tarasenko.dev?subject=Engagement">Email me &rarr;</a>
      </p>

      <h2>What I&rsquo;m useful for</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Debugging an LLM integration or agent loop.</li>
        <li>Reviewing an AI architecture before you build it wrong.</li>
        <li>Diagnosing RAG, tool-calling, prompt, or context problems.</li>
        <li>Setting up practical AI coding workflows for your team.</li>
        <li>Fixing SwiftUI / iOS architecture or build-time issues.</li>
        <li>Untangling a repo, CI, modularization, or DX bottleneck.</li>
        <li>Deciding whether a prototype is worth productionizing.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I&rsquo;m not useful for</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Writing your prompts.</li>
        <li>Picking your model.</li>
        <li>Building a chatbot wrapper around an API.</li>
        <li>Anything that doesn&rsquo;t have a real user on the other end.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Track record</h2>

      <p>
        WhisperBoard 4.8&#9733; on the App Store. mcp-browser-use ~900 stars.
        Codementor 5.0 across 30 sessions. Five years at Uber on server-driven
        UI then payments. In-house now at a large enterprise SaaS company
        running agents in production.
      </p>

      <p>
        Email: <a href="mailto:igor@tarasenko.dev">igor@tarasenko.dev</a>
      </p>

      <Footer />
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>
